Lack of Real-Time Visibility
Another major challenge of traditional expense tracking is the lack of real-time visibility into spending. Many organizations rely on periodic reports, which can be outdated by the time they are reviewed. This delay can hinder decision-making processes and lead to overspending or budget overruns.

Without real-time insights, finance teams face difficulties in monitoring and managing expenses effectively. According to a report by Gartner, organizations that lack real-time visibility into their expenses can experience up to a 30% increase in operational costs due to inefficiencies and missed opportunities for cost savings.

